article.headline: N. Arizona 77, UMKC 62
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Kyle Landry tied his career high with 23 points and also grabbed 14 rebounds as Northern Arizona beat Missouri-Kansas City 77-62 Saturday. Nate Geiser added 14 points and Josh Wilson 10 for the Lumberjacks (2-1), who led 45-27 at halftime and coasted from there. Landry hit eight field goals in 10 tries and was 7-of-10 from the free-throw line while five of his rebounds came on the offensive boards. Dane Brumagin scored 27 points for Missouri-Kansas City (1-2) while Brent Stephens added 17.
